## ğŸ¨ Visual Hierarchy Principles

### Information Architecture
```
Level 1: Core Content (Headlines, Player Names)
  â†’ Font: Bold, Large, High Contrast
  â†’ Color: Black (#212529)

Level 2: Supporting Info (Stats, Descriptions)
  â†’ Font: Normal, Medium, Good Contrast
  â†’ Color: Gray (#495057)

Level 3: Meta Info (Timestamps, Counts)
  â†’ Font: Normal, Small, Subtle
  â†’ Color: Light Gray (#868E96)

Level 4: Decorative (Borders, Backgrounds)
  â†’ Minimal, Neutral
  â†’ Color: Very Light Gray (#F1F3F5)
```

### Contrast Ratios (WCAG AAA)
```
Text on White:
- Normal text: 7:1 minimum
- Large text: 4.5:1 minimum

Interactive Elements:
- 3:1 minimum against background
```

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Implementation Guidelines

### CSS Architecture
```
1. Use Tailwind utilities first
2. Create component-level CSS only when:
   - Complex animations needed
   - Pseudo-elements required
   - Tailwind becomes unreadable
3. Never use inline styles
4. Use CSS variables for theming
```

### Component Composition
```tsx
// âŒ BAD: Monolithic component
function FeedItem() {
  return (
    <div>
      {/* 200 lines of JSX */}
    </div>
  );
}

// âœ… GOOD: Composed components
function FeedItem() {
  return (
    <Card>
      <FeedItemHeader />
      <FeedItemContent />
      <FeedItemFooter />
    </Card>
  );
}
```

---

## âš ï¸ Constraints & Boundaries

### DO âœ…
- Refine existing components
- Improve visual hierarchy
- Enhance micro-interactions
- Optimize spacing and rhythm
- Add meaningful animations (subtle)
- Improve empty/error/loading states
- Enhance accessibility
- Perfect RTL implementation

### DON'T âŒ
- Change business logic
- Modify data structures
- Add new features
- Install new libraries (unless essential for UI)
- Break existing functionality
- Introduce breaking changes
- Redesign from scratch

---

## ğŸ¯ Success Criteria

After improvements:

**Visual:**
- âœ… Looks professional and trustworthy
- âœ… Grass green used effectively (not overwhelming)
- âœ… Clear hierarchy at all levels
- âœ… Consistent spacing and rhythm

**UX:**
- âœ… Actions are obvious and accessible
- âœ… Feedback is immediate and clear
- âœ… Loading/error states are handled gracefully
- âœ… Mobile experience is excellent

**Technical:**
- âœ… No performance regression
- âœ… Accessibility improved
- âœ… RTL perfect
- âœ… Code remains maintainable

